.span10
  - if not @vulnmap
    Metasploit integration not enabled. Contact your administrator to enable (vulnmap configuration setting)
  - else
    %h2 Vulnerabilities
    This is a read-only view of the first 10k vulnerabilities within Metasploits database.
    %p
    %label{:class => "control-label"}
      %a{:href=> '#vulninfomodal', "data-toggle"=>'modal', :class => 'btn btn-info'}
        More Info
    .modal{:id=>'vulninfomodal', :class=>'modal hide fade', :tabindex=>'-1', :role=>'dialog', "aria-labelledby"=>'modal-label', "aria-hidden"=>'true'}
      .modal-header
        %button{:type=>'button', :class=>'close btn btn-default', "data-dismiss"=>"modal", "aria-hidden"=>"true"}
          x
        %h3{:id=>"modal-label"}
          Metasploit Auto Mapping Vulnerabilities
      .modal-body
        To automatically add vulnerabilities from the Metasploit database into your report, you'll need to have one of the reference codes mapped to an existing Serpico finding.
        %p
        A reference code can be added by editing the
        %b Vuln ID
        field of a finding in the Findings Database.
        %p
        %a{:href=> '/master/findings', :class=>'btn btn-default', }
          Go to Findings Database
        %p
    %br
    .table.table-hover
      %table{:style => 'width: 90%'}
        %thead
          %tr
            %td
              %b Vulnerability
            %td
              %b Host
            %td
              %b Port
            %td
              %b References
        %tbody
          - if @vulns
            - @vulns.each do |vuln|
              %tr
                %td{:style => 'width: 50%', :"data-index" => "#{vuln["name"]}", :class=>"searchable"}
                  #{vuln["name"]}
                %td{:style => 'width: 10%', :"data-index" => "#{vuln["host"]}", :class=>"searchable"}
                  #{vuln["host"]}
                %td{:style => 'width: 5%', :"data-index" => "#{vuln["port"]}", :class=>"searchable"}
                  #{vuln["port"]}
                %td{:style => 'width: 35%', :"data-index" => "#{vuln["refs"]}", :class=>"searchable"}
                  #{vuln["refs"]}
